      "role": "user",
      "content": "fair enough. but when u say a lot of these things like \"increased labor costs\" and \"reducing efficiency,\" it sounds like you're basically saying unions are bad for the economy. is there actually a way to look at it where the \"inefficiency\" people talk about is actually just a good thing for society?",
